						<summary>

						<p>Two broken slabs lying in the Durgātemple.</p>						

						<p>1413 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1]335, Vijaya, [Śrāvaṇa] 1,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1413, A.D., July 30.</hi> The details are not verifiable.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register gifts of income to a deity and of oil for burning a lamp in the temple in the month of Vṛiśchika. It refers to the village Yinavaḷi. It is fragmentary and details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
